				<h2>How should I handle an accepted answer that's no longer "correct"?</h2>
<p>What was (or at least at the time appeared to be) a <a href="https://apple.stackexchange.com/a/48412/4395">correct answer</a> to a <a href="https://apple.stackexchange.com/q/30977/4395">question of mine</a> is now (possibly due to software changes by Apple) no longer resolves my question. I've already accepted this answer as the correct one. How should I handle the fact that what it suggests no longer works? </p>

<p>Should I un-accept it? Is that sufficient? </p>

