				<p>You can edit the question to read something like ".... this happens in Mac OS X 10.1.2 (include the minor revision)... " -- or otherwise describe the conditions where the answer remains valid. Then you can ask another question which is based on your old question but with the conditions updated (say, Mac OS X 10.2.3). Remember to link the new question to the old one so that it doesn't get marked as duplicate.</p>
